Vote Data

Vote Data Preparation

Now let’s first clean up the vote data and then do some exploring.

keeplist = c(1,2,4,12,13)
vote_data = vote_data[,keeplist]

vote_data[,2] = str_sub(vote_data[,2] , 2, -2) #remove "" from strings
vote_data[,3] = str_sub(vote_data[,3] , 2, -2)

#converting all columns to their proper formats
vote_data[,3] = as.factor(vote_data[,3])

vote_data[,4:5] = apply(vote_data[,4:5], 2, function(x) as.numeric(as.character((x))))

vote_data$DATUM_ABSTIMMUNG = as.Date(vote_data$DATUM_ABSTIMMUNG, "%d.%m.%Y")

#add a "accepted" columns (>50%)
vote_data = vote_data %>% 
  mutate(ACCEPTED = ifelse(JA_STIMMEN_PROZENT > 50, 1, 0))
vote_data$ACCEPTED = as.factor(vote_data$ACCEPTED)

#remove any NA
vote_data = vote_data[complete.cases(vote_data$JA_STIMMEN_PROZENT),]

Initial Data Exploration

Now that our vote data is cleaned up and properly formatted, we can do some initial data exploration.

First let’s take a look at the total number of votes and how many were accepted.

# stimmbeteiligung over time
#kinds of votes over time
#how manz yes -histogram

ggplot(vote_data, aes(x = ACCEPTED, fill = ACCEPTED)) +
  geom_bar(stat="count")

Improving the graph slightly

ggplot(vote_data, aes(x = ACCEPTED, fill = ACCEPTED)) +
  geom_bar(stat="count") +
  
  labs(x = "Accepted", y = "Number of votes", #add text to graph
  title = "Number of total votes since 1866 divided into rejected and accepted") +
  
  theme(legend.position="none", 
  panel.background = element_blank(),
  axis.line = element_line(colour="#C0C0C0",size=1),
  axis.text=element_text(face="plain",colour="#C0C0C0",size=12), #change size and colour of axis labels (use face="bold" to make bold)
  axis.ticks = element_line(colour="#C0C0C0",size=1) # change colour (and size) of axis ticksggplot change
  )

Next: How were this votes divided over the different kinds of votes?
